columns.name: segments_date
columns.description: Date to which metrics apply. yyyy-MM-dd format, for example, 2018-04-17.

columns.name: segments_device

columns.name: segments_month

columns.name: segments_quarter
columns.description: Quarter as represented by the date of the first day of a quarter. Uses the calendar year for quarters, for example, the second quarter of 2018 starts on 2018-04-01. Formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

columns.name: segments_week
columns.description: Week as defined as Monday through Sunday, and represented by the date of Monday. Formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

columns.name: segments_year
columns.description: Year, formatted as yyyy.

columns.name: segments_conversion_action
columns.description: Resource name of the conversion action.

columns.name: segments_conversion_action_category

columns.name: segments_conversion_action_name

columns.name: product_group_view_resource_name
columns.description: Output only. The resource name of the product group view. Product group view resource names have the form: customers/{customer_id}/productGroupViews/{ad_group_id}~{criterion_id}

columns.name: ad_group_ad_rotation_mode
columns.description: The ad rotation mode of the ad group.

columns.name: ad_group_audience_setting_use_audience_grouped
columns.description: Immutable. If true, this campaign uses an Audience resource for audience targeting. If false, this campaign may use audience segment criteria instead.

columns.name: ad_group_base_ad_group
columns.description: Output only. For draft or experiment ad groups, this field is the resource name of the base ad group from which this ad group was created. If a draft or experiment ad group does not have a base ad group, then this field is null. For base ad groups, this field equals the ad group resource name. This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_campaign
columns.description: Immutable. The campaign to which the ad group belongs.

columns.name: ad_group_cpc_bid_micros
columns.description: The maximum CPC (cost-per-click) bid.

columns.name: ad_group_cpm_bid_micros
columns.description: The maximum CPM (cost-per-thousand viewable impressions) bid.

columns.name: ad_group_cpv_bid_micros
columns.description: The CPV (cost-per-view) bid.

columns.name: ad_group_display_custom_bid_dimension
columns.description: Allows advertisers to specify a targeting dimension on which to place absolute bids. This is only applicable for campaigns that target only the display network and not search.

columns.name: ad_group_effective_cpc_bid_micros
columns.description: Output only. Value will be same as that of the CPC (cost-per-click) bid value when the bidding strategy is one of manual cpc, enhanced cpc, page one promoted or target outrank share, otherwise the value will be null.

columns.name: ad_group_effective_target_cpa_micros
columns.description: Output only. The effective target CPA (cost-per-acquisition). This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_effective_target_cpa_source
columns.description: Output only. Source of the effective target CPA. This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_effective_target_roas
columns.description: Output only. The effective target ROAS (return-on-ad-spend). This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_effective_target_roas_source
columns.description: Output only. Source of the effective target ROAS. This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_excluded_parent_asset_field_types
columns.description: The asset field types that should be excluded from this ad group. Asset links with these field types will not be inherited by this ad group from the upper levels.

columns.name: ad_group_excluded_parent_asset_set_types
columns.description: The asset set types that should be excluded from this ad group. Asset set links with these types will not be inherited by this ad group from the upper levels. Location group types (GMB_DYNAMIC_LOCATION_GROUP, CHAIN_DYNAMIC_LOCATION_GROUP, and STATIC_LOCATION_GROUP) are child types of LOCATION_SYNC. Therefore, if LOCATION_SYNC is set for this field, all location group asset sets are not allowed to be linked to this ad group, and all Location Extension (LE) and Affiliate Location Extensions (ALE) will not be served under this ad group. Only LOCATION_SYNC is currently supported.

columns.name: ad_group_explorer_auto_optimizer_setting_opt_in
columns.description: Indicates whether the optimizer is turned on.

columns.name: ad_group_final_url_suffix
columns.description: URL template for appending params to Final URL.

columns.name: ad_group_id
columns.description: Output only. The ID of the ad group.

columns.name: ad_group_labels
columns.description: Output only. The resource names of labels attached to this ad group.

columns.name: ad_group_name
columns.description: The name of the ad group. This field is required and should not be empty when creating new ad groups. It must contain fewer than 255 UTF-8 full-width characters. It must not contain any null (code point 0x0), NL line feed (code point 0xA) or carriage return (code point 0xD) characters.

columns.name: ad_group_percent_cpc_bid_micros
columns.description: The percent cpc bid amount, expressed as a fraction of the advertised price for some good or service. The valid range for the fraction is [0,1) and the value stored here is 1,000,000 * [fraction].

columns.name: ad_group_resource_name
columns.description: Immutable. The resource name of the ad group. Ad group resource names have the form: customers/{customer_id}/adGroups/{ad_group_id}

columns.name: ad_group_status
columns.description: The status of the ad group.

columns.name: ad_group_target_cpa_micros
columns.description: The target CPA (cost-per-acquisition). If the ad group's campaign bidding strategy is TargetCpa or MaximizeConversions (with its target_cpa field set), then this field overrides the target CPA specified in the campaign's bidding strategy. Otherwise, this value is ignored.

columns.name: ad_group_target_cpm_micros
columns.description: Average amount in micros that the advertiser is willing to pay for every thousand times the ad is shown.

columns.name: ad_group_target_roas
columns.description: The target ROAS (return-on-ad-spend) override. If the ad group's campaign bidding strategy is TargetRoas or MaximizeConversionValue (with its target_roas field set), then this field overrides the target ROAS specified in the campaign's bidding strategy. Otherwise, this value is ignored.

columns.name: ad_group_targeting_setting_target_restrictions

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_audience_audience

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_bid_modifier

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_combined_audience_combined_audience

columns.description: The CPM (cost-per-thousand viewable impressions) bid.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_effective_percent_cpc_bid_micros

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_effective_percent_cpc_bid_source

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_mobile_application_app_id
columns.description: A string that uniquely identifies a mobile application to Google Ads API. The format of this string is "{platform}-{platform_native_id}", where platform is "1" for iOS apps and "2" for Android apps, and where platform_native_id is the mobile application identifier native to the corresponding platform. For iOS, this native identifier is the 9 digit string that appears at the end of an App Store URL (for example, "476943146" for "Flood-It! 2" whose App Store link is "http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/flood-it!-2/id476943146"). For Android, this native identifier is the application's package name (for example, "com.labpixies.colordrips" for "Color Drips" given Google Play link "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.labpixies.colordrips"). A well formed app id for Google Ads API would thus be "1-476943146" for iOS and "2-com.labpixies.colordrips" for Android. This field is required and must be set in CREATE operations.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_mobile_application_name
columns.description: Name of this mobile application.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_negative
columns.description: Immutable. Whether to target (false) or exclude (true) the criterion. This field is immutable. To switch a criterion from positive to negative, remove then re-add it.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_parental_status_type

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_percent_cpc_bid_micros
columns.description: The CPC bid amount, expressed as a fraction of the advertised price for some good or service. The valid range for the fraction is [0,1) and the value stored here is 1,000,000 * [fraction].

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_placement_url

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_position_estimates_estimated_add_clicks_at_first_position_cpc

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_position_estimates_estimated_add_cost_at_first_position_cpc
columns.description: Output only. Estimate of how your cost per week might change when changing your keyword bid to the value in first_position_cpc_micros.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_position_estimates_first_page_cpc_micros
columns.description: Output only. The estimate of the CPC bid required for ad to be shown on first page of search results.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_position_estimates_first_position_cpc_micros
columns.description: Output only. The estimate of the CPC bid required for ad to be displayed in first position, at the top of the first page of search results.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_position_estimates_top_of_page_cpc_micros
columns.description: Output only. The estimate of the CPC bid required for ad to be displayed at the top of the first page of search results.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_quality_info_creative_quality_score

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_quality_info_post_click_quality_score

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_quality_info_quality_score

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_quality_info_search_predicted_ctr
columns.description: Output only. The click-through rate compared to that of other advertisers.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_resource_name
columns.description: Immutable. The resource name of the ad group criterion. Ad group criterion resource names have the form: customers/{customer_id}/adGroupCriteria/{ad_group_id}~{criterion_id}

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_status
columns.description: The status of the criterion. This is the status of the ad group criterion entity, set by the client. Note: UI reports may incorporate additional information that affects whether a criterion is eligible to run. In some cases a criterion that's REMOVED in the API can still show as enabled in the UI. For example, campaigns by default show to users of all age ranges unless excluded. The UI will show each age range as "enabled", since they're eligible to see the ads; but AdGroupCriterion.status will show "removed", since no positive criterion was added.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_system_serving_status
columns.description: Output only. Serving status of the criterion.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_topic_path
columns.description: The category to target or exclude. Each subsequent element in the array describes a more specific sub-category. For example, "Pets & Animals", "Pets", "Dogs" represents the "Pets & Animals/Pets/Dogs" category.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_topic_topic_constant
columns.description: The Topic Constant resource name.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_tracking_url_template
columns.description: The URL template for constructing a tracking URL.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_type
columns.description: Output only. The type of the criterion.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_url_custom_parameters
columns.description: The list of mappings used to substitute custom parameter tags in a tracking_url_template, final_urls, or mobile_final_urls.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_user_interest_user_interest_category
columns.description: The UserInterest resource name.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_user_list_user_list
columns.description: The User List resource name.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_webpage_conditions
columns.description: Conditions, or logical expressions, for webpage targeting. The list of webpage targeting conditions are and-ed together when evaluated for targeting. An empty list of conditions indicates all pages of the campaign's website are targeted. This field is required for CREATE operations and is prohibited on UPDATE operations.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_webpage_coverage_percentage
columns.description: Website criteria coverage percentage. This is the computed percentage of website coverage based on the website target, negative website target and negative keywords in the ad group and campaign. For instance, when coverage returns as 1, it indicates it has 100% coverage. This field is read-only.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_webpage_criterion_name
columns.description: The name of the criterion that is defined by this parameter. The name value will be used for identifying, sorting and filtering criteria with this type of parameters. This field is required for CREATE operations and is prohibited on UPDATE operations.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_webpage_sample_sample_urls
columns.description: Webpage sample urls

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_youtube_channel_channel_id
columns.description: The YouTube uploader channel id or the channel code of a YouTube channel.

columns.name: ad_group_criterion_youtube_video_video_id
columns.description: YouTube video id as it appears on the YouTube watch page.

columns.name: campaign_accessible_bidding_strategy
columns.description: Output only. Resource name of AccessibleBiddingStrategy, a read-only view of the unrestricted attributes of the attached portfolio bidding strategy identified by 'bidding_strategy'. Empty, if the campaign does not use a portfolio strategy. Unrestricted strategy attributes are available to all customers with whom the strategy is shared and are read from the AccessibleBiddingStrategy resource. In contrast, restricted attributes are only available to the owner customer of the strategy and their managers. Restricted attributes can only be read from the BiddingStrategy resource.

columns.name: campaign_ad_serving_optimization_status
columns.description: The ad serving optimization status of the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_advertising_channel_sub_type
columns.description: Immutable. Optional refinement to advertising_channel_type. Must be a valid sub-type of the parent channel type. Can be set only when creating campaigns. After campaign is created, the field can not be changed.

columns.name: campaign_advertising_channel_type
columns.description: Immutable. The primary serving target for ads within the campaign. The targeting options can be refined in network_settings. This field is required and should not be empty when creating new campaigns. Can be set only when creating campaigns. After the campaign is created, the field can not be changed.

columns.name: campaign_app_campaign_setting_app_id
columns.description: Immutable. A string that uniquely identifies a mobile application.

columns.name: campaign_app_campaign_setting_app_store
columns.description: Immutable. The application store that distributes this specific app.

columns.name: campaign_app_campaign_setting_bidding_strategy_goal_type
columns.description: Represents the goal which the bidding strategy of this app campaign should optimize towards.

columns.name: campaign_audience_setting_use_audience_grouped
columns.description: Immutable. If true, this campaign uses an Audience resource for audience targeting. If false, this campaign may use audience segment criteria instead.

columns.name: campaign_base_campaign
columns.description: Output only. The resource name of the base campaign of a draft or experiment campaign. For base campaigns, this is equal to resource_name. This field is read-only.

columns.name: campaign_bidding_strategy
columns.description: Portfolio bidding strategy used by campaign.

columns.name: campaign_bidding_strategy_system_status
columns.description: Output only. The system status of the campaign's bidding strategy.

columns.name: campaign_bidding_strategy_type
columns.description: Output only. The type of bidding strategy. A bidding strategy can be created by setting either the bidding scheme to create a standard bidding strategy or the bidding_strategy field to create a portfolio bidding strategy. This field is read-only.

columns.name: campaign_campaign_budget
columns.description: The budget of the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_campaign_group
columns.description: The campaign group this campaign belongs to.

columns.name: campaign_commission_commission_rate_micros
columns.description: Commission rate defines the portion of the conversion value that the advertiser will be billed. A commission rate of x should be passed into this field as (x * 1,000,000). For example, 106,000 represents a commission rate of 0.106 (10.6%).

columns.name: campaign_dynamic_search_ads_setting_domain_name
columns.description: Required. The Internet domain name that this setting represents, for example, "google.com" or "www.google.com".

columns.name: campaign_dynamic_search_ads_setting_feeds
columns.description: The list of page feeds associated with the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_dynamic_search_ads_setting_language_code
columns.description: Required. The language code specifying the language of the domain, for example, "en".

columns.name: campaign_dynamic_search_ads_setting_use_supplied_urls_only
columns.description: Whether the campaign uses advertiser supplied URLs exclusively.

columns.name: campaign_end_date
columns.description: The last day of the campaign in serving customer's timezone in YYYY-MM-DD format. On create, defaults to 2037-12-30, which means the campaign will run indefinitely. To set an existing campaign to run indefinitely, set this field to 2037-12-30.

columns.name: campaign_excluded_parent_asset_field_types
columns.description: The asset field types that should be excluded from this campaign. Asset links with these field types will not be inherited by this campaign from the upper level.

columns.name: campaign_excluded_parent_asset_set_types
columns.description: The asset set types that should be excluded from this campaign. Asset set links with these types will not be inherited by this campaign from the upper level. Location group types (GMB_DYNAMIC_LOCATION_GROUP, CHAIN_DYNAMIC_LOCATION_GROUP, and STATIC_LOCATION_GROUP) are child types of LOCATION_SYNC. Therefore, if LOCATION_SYNC is set for this field, all location group asset sets are not allowed to be linked to this campaign, and all Location Extension (LE) and Affiliate Location Extensions (ALE) will not be served under this campaign. Only LOCATION_SYNC is currently supported.

columns.name: campaign_experiment_type
columns.description: Output only. The type of campaign: normal, draft, or experiment.

columns.name: campaign_final_url_suffix
columns.description: Suffix used to append query parameters to landing pages that are served with parallel tracking.

columns.name: campaign_frequency_caps
columns.description: A list that limits how often each user will see this campaign's ads.

columns.name: campaign_geo_target_type_setting_negative_geo_target_type
columns.description: The setting used for negative geotargeting in this particular campaign.

columns.name: campaign_geo_target_type_setting_positive_geo_target_type
columns.description: The setting used for positive geotargeting in this particular campaign.

columns.name: campaign_hotel_setting_hotel_center_id
columns.description: Immutable. The linked Hotel Center account.

columns.name: campaign_id
columns.description: Output only. The ID of the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_labels
columns.description: Output only. The resource names of labels attached to this campaign.

columns.name: campaign_local_campaign_setting_location_source_type
columns.description: The location source type for this local campaign.

columns.name: campaign_local_services_campaign_settings_category_bids
columns.description: Categorical level bids associated with MANUAL_CPA bidding strategy.

columns.name: campaign_manual_cpa
columns.description: Standard Manual CPA bidding strategy. Manual bidding strategy that allows advertiser to set the bid per advertiser-specified action. Supported only for Local Services campaigns.

columns.name: campaign_manual_cpc_enhanced_cpc_enabled
columns.description: Whether bids are to be enhanced based on conversion optimizer data.

columns.name: campaign_manual_cpm
columns.description: Standard Manual CPM bidding strategy. Manual impression-based bidding where user pays per thousand impressions.

columns.name: campaign_manual_cpv
columns.description: Output only. A bidding strategy that pays a configurable amount per video view.

columns.name: campaign_maximize_conversion_value_target_roas
columns.description: Output only. The target return on ad spend (ROAS) option. If set, the bid strategy will maximize revenue while averaging the target return on ad spend. If the target ROAS is high, the bid strategy may not be able to spend the full budget. If the target ROAS is not set, the bid strategy will aim to achieve the highest possible ROAS for the budget.

columns.name: campaign_maximize_conversions_target_cpa_micros
columns.description: Output only. The target cost per acquisition (CPA) option. This is the average amount that you would like to spend per acquisition.

columns.name: campaign_name
columns.description: The name of the campaign. This field is required and should not be empty when creating new campaigns. It must not contain any null (code point 0x0), NL line feed (code point 0xA) or carriage return (code point 0xD) characters.

columns.name: campaign_network_settings_target_content_network
columns.description: Whether ads will be served on specified placements in the Google Display Network. Placements are specified using the Placement criterion.

columns.name: campaign_network_settings_target_google_search
columns.description: Whether ads will be served with google.com search results.

columns.name: campaign_network_settings_target_partner_search_network
columns.description: Whether ads will be served on the Google Partner Network. This is available only to some select Google partner accounts.

columns.name: campaign_network_settings_target_search_network
columns.description: Whether ads will be served on partner sites in the Google Search Network (requires target_google_search to also be true).

columns.name: campaign_optimization_goal_setting_optimization_goal_types
columns.description: The list of optimization goal types.

columns.name: campaign_optimization_score
columns.description: Output only. Optimization score of the campaign. Optimization score is an estimate of how well a campaign is set to perform. It ranges from 0% (0.0) to 100% (1.0), with 100% indicating that the campaign is performing at full potential. This field is null for unscored campaigns. See "About optimization score" at https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9061546. This field is read-only.

columns.name: campaign_payment_mode
columns.description: Payment mode for the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_percent_cpc_cpc_bid_ceiling_micros
columns.description: Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. This is an optional field entered by the advertiser and specified in local micros. Note: A zero value is interpreted in the same way as having bid_ceiling undefined.

columns.name: campaign_percent_cpc_enhanced_cpc_enabled
columns.description: Adjusts the bid for each auction upward or downward, depending on the likelihood of a conversion. Individual bids may exceed cpc_bid_ceiling_micros, but the average bid amount for a campaign should not.

columns.name: campaign_performance_max_upgrade_performance_max_campaign
columns.description: Output only. Indicates which Performance Max campaign the campaign is upgraded to.

columns.name: campaign_performance_max_upgrade_pre_upgrade_campaign
columns.description: Output only. Indicates legacy campaign upgraded to Performance Max.

columns.name: campaign_performance_max_upgrade_status
columns.description: Output only. The upgrade status of a campaign requested to be upgraded to Performance Max.

columns.name: campaign_primary_status
columns.description: Output only. The primary status of the campaign. Provides insight into why a campaign is not serving or not serving optimally. Modification to the campaign and its related entities might take a while to be reflected in this status.

columns.name: campaign_primary_status_reasons
columns.description: Output only. The primary status reasons of the campaign. Provides insight into why a campaign is not serving or not serving optimally. These reasons are aggregated to determine an overall CampaignPrimaryStatus.

columns.name: campaign_real_time_bidding_setting_opt_in
columns.description: Whether the campaign is opted in to real-time bidding.

columns.name: campaign_resource_name
columns.description: Immutable. The resource name of the campaign. Campaign resource names have the form: customers/{customer_id}/campaigns/{campaign_id}

columns.name: campaign_selective_optimization_conversion_actions
columns.description: The selected set of conversion actions for optimizing this campaign.

columns.name: campaign_serving_status
columns.description: Output only. The ad serving status of the campaign.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_campaign_priority
columns.description: Priority of the campaign. Campaigns with numerically higher priorities take precedence over those with lower priorities. This field is required for Shopping campaigns, with values between 0 and 2, inclusive. This field is optional for Smart Shopping campaigns, but must be equal to 3 if set.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_enable_local
columns.description: Whether to include local products.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_feed_label
columns.description: Feed label of products to include in the campaign. Only one of feed_label or sales_country can be set. If used instead of sales_country, the feed_label field accepts country codes in the same format for example: 'XX'. Otherwise can be any string used for feed label in Google Merchant Center.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_merchant_id
columns.description: Immutable. ID of the Merchant Center account. This field is required for create operations. This field is immutable for Shopping campaigns.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_sales_country
columns.description: Sales country of products to include in the campaign. Only one of feed_label or sales_country can be set. Field is immutable except for clearing. Once this field is cleared, you must use feed_label if you want to set the sales country.

columns.name: campaign_shopping_setting_use_vehicle_inventory
columns.description: Immutable. Whether to target Vehicle Listing inventory.

columns.name: campaign_start_date
columns.description: The date when campaign started in serving customer's timezone in YYYY-MM-DD format.

columns.name: campaign_status
columns.description: The status of the campaign. When a new campaign is added, the status defaults to ENABLED.

columns.name: campaign_target_cpa_cpc_bid_ceiling_micros
columns.description: Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.

columns.name: campaign_target_cpa_cpc_bid_floor_micros
columns.description: Minimum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.

columns.name: campaign_target_cpa_target_cpa_micros
columns.description: Average CPA target. This target should be greater than or equal to minimum billable unit based on the currency for the account.

columns.name: campaign_target_cpm
columns.description: A bidding strategy that automatically optimizes cost per thousand impressions.

columns.name: campaign_target_impression_share_cpc_bid_ceiling_micros
columns.description: The highest CPC bid the automated bidding system is permitted to specify. This is a required field entered by the advertiser that sets the ceiling and specified in local micros.

columns.name: campaign_target_impression_share_location
columns.description: The targeted location on the search results page.

columns.name: campaign_target_impression_share_location_fraction_micros
columns.description: The chosen fraction of ads to be shown in the targeted location in micros. For example, 1% equals 10,000.

columns.name: campaign_target_roas_cpc_bid_ceiling_micros
columns.description: Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.

columns.name: campaign_target_roas_cpc_bid_floor_micros
columns.description: Minimum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.

columns.name: campaign_target_roas_target_roas
columns.description: Output only. The chosen revenue (based on conversion data) per unit of spend.

columns.name: campaign_target_spend_cpc_bid_ceiling_micros
columns.description: Output only. Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.

columns.name: campaign_target_spend_target_spend_micros
columns.description: Output only. The spend target under which to maximize clicks. A TargetSpend bidder will attempt to spend the smaller of this value or the natural throttling spend amount. If not specified, the budget is used as the spend target. This field is deprecated and should no longer be used. See https://ads-developers.googleblog.com/2020/05/reminder-about-sunset-creation-of.html for details.

columns.name: campaign_targeting_setting_target_restrictions
columns.description: The per-targeting-dimension setting to restrict the reach of your campaign or ad group.

columns.name: campaign_tracking_setting_tracking_url
columns.description: Output only. The url used for dynamic tracking.

columns.name: campaign_tracking_url_template
columns.description: The URL template for constructing a tracking URL.

columns.name: campaign_url_custom_parameters
columns.description: The list of mappings used to substitute custom parameter tags in a tracking_url_template, final_urls, or mobile_final_urls.

columns.name: campaign_url_expansion_opt_out
columns.description: Represents opting out of URL expansion to more targeted URLs. If opted out (true), only the final URLs in the asset group or URLs specified in the advertiser's Google Merchant Center or business data feeds are targeted. If opted in (false), the entire domain will be targeted. This field can only be set for Performance Max campaigns, where the default value is false.

columns.name: campaign_vanity_pharma_vanity_pharma_display_url_mode
columns.description: The display mode for vanity pharma URLs.

columns.name: campaign_vanity_pharma_vanity_pharma_text
columns.description: The text that will be displayed in display URL of the text ad when website description is the selected display mode for vanity pharma URLs.

columns.name: campaign_video_brand_safety_suitability
columns.description: Output only. 3-Tier Brand Safety setting for the campaign.

columns.name: metrics_all_conversions
columns.description: The total number of conversions. This includes all conversions regardless of the value of include_in_conversions_metric.

columns.name: metrics_all_conversions_value
columns.description: The value of all conversions.

columns.name: metrics_conversions
columns.description: The number of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.

columns.name: metrics_conversions_value
columns.description: The value of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.

columns.name: metrics_cross_device_conversions
columns.description: Conversions from when a customer clicks on a Google Ads ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in all_conversions.

columns.name: metrics_value_per_all_conversions
columns.description: The value of all conversions divided by the number of all conversions.

columns.name: metrics_value_per_conversion
columns.description: The value of conversions divided by the number of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.

columns.name: metrics_view_through_conversions
columns.description: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees an image or rich media ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (for example, clicking on) another ad.
